	<Sentence>
		<value>If you have breathing problems and you:  - Are short of breath most of the time  - Get short of breath when you walk 150 feet or less  - Have been in the hospital for breathing problems recently  - Use oxygen at home, even if just at night or with exercise   If you were in the hospital for your breathing problems and had:  - Pneumonia  - Chest surgery  - A collapsed lung    Also talk to your doctor if you plan to travel in a place at a high altitude (such as Colorado or Utah).</value>
